data.name: lblProtectionHelpMeChoose.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Users who obtain the prefab will be able to view, edit, and override tags if it is unprotected. Such access enables users to modify the content, repackage it as their own, or borrow concepts from the tag files.

Protected - Option required to prevent users from creating derivatives, reusing tags, or redistributing content falsely. Also forces any project it is included in to be obfuscated when compiled.

No Protection - Option recommended for prefabs created with the intent to be used along with a tutorial. It is also recommended for creators who wish to share tag information publicly.

Supplying a password in the Recovery Password field is strongly recommended. Protected prefabs can be accessed and tags recovered with this password. The password should be secure, for anyone who obtains it will have full access to the prefab. The password can be remembered by Prometheus if desired.

data.name: infoScreenshot.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Create a custom image that will represent the prefab. If no custom image is selected, one will be automatically generated.

Manually creating an image is highly recommended â€“ an automatically generated image will not represent the prefab nearly as well as a custom one.

data.name: infoProtectionPasswordRemembered.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Store the prefab's recovery password in Prometheus' Password Manager.

This option is recommended as it aids in recovering the contents of a prefab, on this machine, if the recovery password is forgotten.

data.name: infoProtectionNoProtection.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Place no restrictions on the prefab, allowing users access to view, edit, override, and redistribute prefab tags at will.

Option recommended for prefabs created with the intent to be used along with a tutorial. It is also recommended for creators who wish to share tag information publicly.

data.name: infoProtectionProtected.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Restrict the prefab tags from being directly accessed by users.

Option required to prevent users from creating derivatives, reusing tags, or redistributing content falsely.

Note: When a protected prefab is included in a map, that map is forced into being obfuscated.

data.name: infoRecoveryPassword.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Set a recovery password to enable viewing of the prefab's custom tags and decompilation of the prefab.

A strong, but memorable, password is recommended. Any user with the password will be able to peruse its custom tags.

This field is not required to create a prefab, but it is strongly recommended.

data.name: infoPrefabRootTag.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Select the root tag of the object that defines this prefab.

All dependencies required to compile the prefab will be included. For options regarding which tags are packaged with the prefab, use the "Customize Packaged Tags" feature.

data.name: infoAllowDownloads.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Allowing users to download the prefab through the HaloDev site helps spread creative content more easily and quickly, assuring the author receives recognition, and increasing the range of content users may have in their own creations.

Giving back to the community goes a long way to making it stronger and bigger. By contributing hard work back to the community, quality content is likely to end up in a multitude of maps, greatly extending the content's original usage and providing a better experience for all.

HaloDev ID Required.

Note that reporting information about the prefab to the database means individually identifiable information is required and included automatically. See the "Include Author Info in Prefab" InfoTip for details.

data.name: infoReportPrefab.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Reporting the prefab to the HaloDev Prefab Database assists in verifying authorship, providing the prefab for download (with permission), and adding information about the prefab to the public library of user created content.

The database acts as a library for all opt-in user content information created with Prometheus. By allowing the prefab's information to be added, the community is strengthened and potential users are provided the opportunity to more easily find quality, creative content.

HaloDev ID Required.

Note that reporting information about the prefab to the database means individually identifiable information is required and included automatically. See the "Include Author Info in Prefab" InfoTip for details.

data.name: infoIncludeAuthorInfo.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Include individually identifiable information with the prefab to provide proof of authorship.

The information included comes from the active HaloDev ID account. The two pieces of information included are user ID and pseudonym.

User ID Number: #######
Pseudonym: Name

Note: Information automatically included if the prefab is being reported to the HaloDev Prefab Database.
